description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/18771/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'marine engine', in the Global geography.;This market connects the supply chain of marine engines from their production till the place they are employed and used. Default transportation based on ISIC classification is used for the product. Marine engine is an internal combustion engine, dedicated for a fishing vessel.

Activity starts after the production of marine engine.

Activity ends with the provision of marine engine to its relevant consumers.
